# Widget Conventions

## Widget Hierarchy

1. **Screens** (`/lib/screens/`) - Top-level navigation targets
2. **Widgets** (`/lib/widgets/`) - Reusable components
3. **Shared Widgets** (`/lib/widgets/shared/`) - Generic components

## ConsumerWidget Pattern

**Use `ConsumerWidget` only when you need provider access.** If a widget doesn't need to access providers, use `StatelessWidget` instead - it's lighter, clearer, and follows the "props down, events up" pattern.

### When to Use ConsumerWidget

Use `ConsumerWidget` when you need to access Riverpod providers:

```dart
class MyWidget extends ConsumerWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key, required this.param});

  final int param;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final data = ref.watch(someProvider); // Needs provider access
    return Widget();
  }
}
```

### When to Use StatelessWidget

Use `StatelessWidget` when the widget receives all data via props (no provider access needed):

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT - StatelessWidget is appropriate when no provider access needed
class AppHeader extends StatelessWidget {
  const AppHeader({
    super.key,
    required this.title,
    this.onSearchPressed,
    this.onBookmarkPressed,
  });

  final String title;
  final VoidCallback? onSearchPressed;
  final VoidCallback? onBookmarkPressed;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    // No ref.watch(), ref.read(), or ref.listen() needed
    // All data comes from props
    return Widget();
  }
}
```

**Benefits of using StatelessWidget when appropriate:**

- Better performance (lighter widget)
- Clearer dependencies (explicit props vs implicit providers)
- Easier testing (pure presentation components)
- Follows React-like patterns (props down, events up)

## ConsumerStatefulWidget Pattern

**Use `ConsumerStatefulWidget` only when you need both stateful behavior AND provider access.** If you need state but not providers, use `StatefulWidget`. If you need providers but not state, use `ConsumerWidget`.

### When to Use ConsumerStatefulWidget

Use `ConsumerStatefulWidget` when you need both state management and provider access:

```dart
class MyWidget extends ConsumerStatefulWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});

  @override
  ConsumerState<MyWidget> createState() => _MyWidgetState();
}

class _MyWidgetState extends ConsumerState<MyWidget> {
  int _counter = 0; // Local state

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final data = ref.watch(someProvider); // Provider access
    return Widget();
  }
}
```

### When to Use StatefulWidget

Use `StatefulWidget` when you need state but not provider access:

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT - StatefulWidget when no provider access needed
class MyWidget extends StatefulWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});

  @override
  State<MyWidget> createState() => _MyWidgetState();
}

class _MyWidgetState extends State<MyWidget> {
  int _counter = 0; // Local state only

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    // No ref parameter needed
    return Widget();
  }
}
```

## Responsive Sizing

Use constants from [constants.dart](mdc:lib/constants.dart) for responsive design:

```dart
final screenWidth = MediaQuery.of(context).size.width;
final scaleFactor = screenWidth / referenceScreenWidth;
final fontSize = (baseFontSize * scaleFactor).clamp(
  minAyahFontSize,
  maxAyahFontSize,
);
```

### Key Sizing Constants

- `referenceScreenWidth` / `referenceScreenHeight` - Base dimensions
- `baseFontSize` - Starting font size
- `min/maxAyahFontSize` - Font size bounds
- `baseLineHeight` - Line height multiplier

## Screen Structure

**ALL screens MUST wrap their `SafeArea` (or root widget) in a `Directionality` widget** with `textDirection: TextDirection.rtl` to ensure consistent RTL behavior throughout the screen.

### Required Pattern

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT - Directionality wrapper at root level
return Scaffold(
  body: Directionality(
    textDirection: TextDirection.rtl,
    child: SafeArea(
      child: Column(
        children: [
          AppHeader(title: 'عنوان', showBackButton: true),
          Expanded(
            child: // ... content
          ),
        ],
      ),
    ),
  ),
);
```

### Common Mistake

```dart
// ❌ INCORRECT - Missing Directionality wrapper
return Scaffold(
  body: SafeArea(
    child: Column(
      children: [
        AppHeader(title: 'عنوان', showBackButton: true),
        // ... content
      ],
    ),
  ),
);
```

**Why**: Without the root-level `Directionality` widget, `AppHeader` and other top-level widgets may not inherit RTL directionality correctly, leading to inconsistent layout and text direction.

### Compliance Status

**Screens WITH Directionality wrapper (✅ Correct)**:

- [ayah_details_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/ayah_details_screen.dart)
- [bookmarks_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/bookmarks_screen.dart)
- [explore_hub_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/explore_hub_screen.dart)
- [search_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/search_screen.dart)
- [settings_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/settings_screen.dart)
- [topic_detail_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/topic_detail_screen.dart)

**Screens WITHOUT Directionality wrapper (❌ Needs Fixing)**:

- [audio_config_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/audio_config_screen.dart) - Missing wrapper around SafeArea
- [selection_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/selection_screen.dart) - Missing wrapper around SafeArea
- [statistics_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/statistics_screen.dart) - Missing wrapper around SafeArea (has Directionality only inside Expanded child)

**Special Cases**:

- [mushaf_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/mushaf_screen.dart) - Returns Stack containing Scaffold, needs Directionality wrapper around SafeArea inside Stack
- [splash_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/splash_screen.dart) - Simple loading screen (may be acceptable, but should still follow pattern for consistency)

## RTL Layout

The app uses RTL by default (set in [main.dart](mdc:lib/main.dart)):

```dart
home: const Directionality(
  textDirection: TextDirection.rtl,
  child: SplashScreen(),
),
```

Widgets should respect RTL layout automatically. Use `Align` and `Padding` instead of hardcoded left/right positioning.

## AsyncValue Handling

When consuming async providers:

```dart
final asyncValue = ref.watch(pageDataProvider(pageNumber));

return asyncValue.when(
  data: (data) => BuildWidget(data),
  loading: () => const CircularProgressIndicator(),
  error: (error, stack) => ErrorWidget(error),
);
```

Or use `.whenData()` for specific scenarios in [mushaf_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/mushaf_screen.dart):

```dart
asyncPageData.whenData((PageData pageData) {
  // Handle data
});
```

## Immutability

All data passed to widgets should be immutable:

```dart
@immutable
class MyData {
  final String text;
  const MyData({required this.text});
}
```

## Key Usage

Use `super.key` in constructors:

```dart
const MyWidget({super.key, required this.param});
```

## BuildContext Safety

Check `context.mounted` before async navigation:

```dart
if (context.mounted) {
  Navigator.pop(context);
}
```
